cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Name: AG2549F ALAB RFT Multi Supplier Framework Agreement for the Provision of Technical Expertise to Evaluate the Ecological, Environmental and Technical Impact of Aquaculture Projects
cac:ProcurementProject.cbc:Description: The Aquaculture Licences Appeals Board (ALAB) wishes to procure services for the Provision of Technical Expertise to Evaluate the Ecological, Environmental and Technical Impact of Aquaculture Projects. Suppliers can tender for any one lot, or any combination of lots or all lots. Lots 1 and 2, Marine Ecology and Environment - Shellfish and Algae and Marine Ecology and Environment - Finfish, are likely to be the most frequently required services and will, in most cases, be sufficient to provide the technical expertise required. It is estimated that services under Lots 1 and 2 will be required at a frequency of between 5 - 20 times per annum. The other Lots 3 - 9 inclusive relate to more specialised services that may arise on occasion and may be for the purpose of supplementing reports produced in the context of Lots 1 and 2. It should be noted that the successful tenderer may be required to give a presentation of any reports prepared to the Board Members of ALAB.
